    "question": "The mean of ten positive numbers is 16. When another number is added, the mean becomes 18. Find the eleventh number",
    "option": {
      "a": "3",
      "b": "16",
      "c": "38",
      "d": "30",
      "e": null
    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "c",
    "solution": "Mean of 10 numbers = 16\n\nThe total sum of numbers = 16 x 10 = 160\n\nMean of 11 numbers = 18\n\nTotal sum of numbers = 11 x 18\n\n= 198\n\nThe 11th no. = 198 - 160\n\n= 38",
    "examtype": "utme",
    "examyear": "2021"
  },
