    "question": "If (x + 2) and (x - 1) are factors of the expression Lx+2kx<sup>2</sup>+24\n, find the values of L and k.",
    "option": {
      "a": "l = -12, k = -6",
      "b": "l = -2 , k = 1",
      "c": "l = -2 , k = -1",
      "d": "l = 0, k = 1",
      "e": null
    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "a",
    "solution": "Given (x + 2) and (x - 1), i.e. x = -2 or +1\n\nwhen x = -2\n\nL(-2) + 2k(-2)<sup>2</sup>  + 24 = 0\n\nf(-2) = -2L + 8k = -24...(i)\n\n\nAnd x = 1\nL(1) + 2k(1) + 24 = 0\n\n\nf(1):L + 2k = -24...(ii)\n\nSubst, L = -24 - 2k in eqn (i)\n\n-2(-24 - 2k) + 8k = -24\n\n+48 + 4k + 8k = -24\n\n12k = -24 - 48 = -72\n\nk = −72/12\nk = -6\n\nwhere L = -24 - 2k\n\nL = -24 - 2(-6)\n\nL = -24 + 12\n\nL = -12\n\nThat is; K = -6 and L = -12",
    "examtype": " ",
    "examyear": "2021"
  },
